<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
Type of 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. recurvispina" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="recurvispina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. recurvispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 1949 is destroyed or lost (
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, C. F." journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" pagination="139 - 153" refId="B8002352" refString="Wu, C. F., 1962. Biological investigation report of Yunnan (Order Plecoptera. Acta Entomologica Sinica 11: 139 - 153" title="Biological investigation report of Yunnan (Order Plecoptera" volume="11" year="1962">Wu 1962</bibRefCitation>
). The description in the original literature is not detailed and the drawing is very poor (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F8002464" captionText="Figure 2. Rhopalopsole recurvispina (Wu, 1949), nom. dubium. A Male terminalia, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, ventral view; C Male terminalia, lateral view. Modified from Wu (1949)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711846" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">2</figureCitation>
). The distinguishing characteristics of this species are also not sufficient: there is no obvious sclerotized area on tergum 9 of this species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F8002464" captionText="Figure 2. Rhopalopsole recurvispina (Wu, 1949), nom. dubium. A Male terminalia, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, ventral view; C Male terminalia, lateral view. Modified from Wu (1949)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711846" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">2</figureCitation>
A). We therefore regard 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. recurvispina" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="recurvispina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. recurvispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a nomen dubium after we failed many times to collect this species from the type locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
